article.headline: Coppin St 75, Florida A&M 70
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) -- Coppin State guard Talmadge Bell scored 17 points to lead Coppin State to victory over Florida A&M 75-70 Monday. The win was Coppin State's second in as many contests after dropping the first 12 games of the season. Eagles (2-12, 2-1) players Darryl Proctor scored 15 points and Tywain McKee had 16 also contributed for Coppin State with double-digit point totals. Proctor also posted a game-high 9 rebounds. For the Rattlers (6-9, 2-2) , Rome Sanders led the way with 19 points. The Rattlers outrebounded Coppin State 28-27 and also won the turnover battle 10-16. Powered by 55.2 percent shooting from the field in the first half of play, including 47.1 percent from three-point range, the Eagles took a 42-28 lead into halftime. Bell paced the visiting squad with 14 points in the games first 20 minutes.
